DataElement.preferredName: Reference Object Outcome Data ACT I2B2 CDM Laboratory Result Low Modifier Code
DataElement.preferredDefinition: Something referred to; the object of a reference.:The result of an action._A collection or single item of factual information, derived from measurement or research, from which conclusions may be drawn._Modifier for RAW_NORMAL_RANGE_LOW values. For numeric results one of the following needs to be true: 1) Both RAW_MODIFIER_LOW and RAW_MODIFIER_HIGH contain EQ (e.g., normal values fall in the range 3-10) 2) RAW_MODIFIER_LOW contains GT or GE and RAW_MODIFIER_HIGH contains NO (e.g., normal values are >3 with no upper boundary) 3) RAW_MODIFIER_HIGH contains LT or LE and RAW_MODIFIER_LOW contains NO (e.g., normal values are <=10 with no lower boundary)
